    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-05-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-05-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="479"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d479">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">701.4193/57</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">British Embassy</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="10" xml:id="d479fn10">Handed to the Under Secretary of State by the
                        Counselor of the British Embassy, May 15.</note>
                </head>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Aide-Mémoire</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Japanese Government having notified His Majesty’s Government of their intention
                    to raise status of Japanese Legation in China within the next few weeks and
                    having expressed hope that His Majesty’s Government would do likewise, His
                    Majesty’s Embassy have been instructed to inform the United States Government,
                    in accordance with the existing understanding between the two Governments in
                    regard to this matter, that, in view of the Japanese decision and of the fact
                    that the Union of Soviet Socialist Republics and Italian Governments already
                    maintain Embassies in China, His Majesty’s Government do not feel able further
                    to delay similar action.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-05-14">14 May,
                            1935</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
